# Premium Artistic Direction

- Every client site should feel premium, intentional, and visually elevated.
- Establish a unique art direction per client before implementation: imagery mood, icon style, type personality, and texture/motif language.
- Use high-quality images that match the chosen art direction; avoid generic stock-photo mixes.
- Define a distinct icon system per client (stroke/fill style, corner geometry, visual weight) and keep usage consistent.
- Use strong visual hierarchy, generous spacing, and restrained color contrast to signal premium quality.
- Prefer fewer, high-impact visual elements over crowded layouts or trend-heavy effects.
- Keep aesthetics compatible with performance goals through optimized image sizing and selective decorative effects.
